    "note": "Figure 4 IS an exact radial Gaussian at printed precision — but only inside a narrow sigma window the book never prints, and the window that works under round-to-2dp is DISJOINT from the one that works under truncation. A team deriving the kernel from its own fit lands outside the other team's window and gets a different field, silently. The printed 25 values are the only thing two implementations can both reach, so the kernel is pinned verbatim. (Reconciles the open question between our earlier reading — 'the values match no clean formula' — and anrbj666's 'exact Gaussian': theirs is right about the shape, ours about the reproducibility. Both conclusions point here.)"
